  "elapsed_s": 9.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, it was the people were on the boat and the British-- small crew came on the boat from a British warship, and they thought that we'll be in trouble now.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And when the-- when the commander, the young lieutenant, who gives the order to proceed to the next British port and gave the Captain the order in writing.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Suddenly, the British start to lead a song sung that which was familiar to them.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was-- It was very familiar to them.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was 'God Save the King.' Our people sang 'God Save the King' of this foolish British Navy, which sent us home.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was our most traveled of all ships.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were people from Vienna and from Budapest some, but mainly Vienna and mainly Orthodox people from the [INAUDIBLE] which we wanted to take along for a long time, because they were traveling with [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But we took them on the And the people arrived [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] by boat and they came by boat, I think.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It could be they came by train because by then, the permission to bring them by train if you had a boat in the port.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They went in sealed trains.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I have a photo of this.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I don't remember any more of how they came, but while the vessel in tow, on troops, there came reports of a serious disease.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they went to Cosenza to be boarding the ships there, and there it was assembled.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "First it was told that they have-- had some-- I don't remember the name of the disease now.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Very serious disease, very infectious.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And then it was that-- the disease was scarlet fever, which was a very dangerous disease at that time, too.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
